ACS Mapping

Gwendolyn Reynolds

April 27, 2017

I decided I wanted to learn how to do geospatial mapping using census data. I’m playing with making maps using the American Community Survey. First up, I map the percent of households with children who received SNAP/Food Stamps. I use this tutorial plus inspo from Jon Zadra’s pretty Oregon graphs and analysis.

Source: American Community Survey Table B22002, “RECEIPT OF FOOD STAMPS/SNAP IN THE PAST 12 MONTHS BY POVERTY STATUS IN THE PAST 12 MONTHS FOR HOUSEHOLDS,” 2011-2015 American Community Survey 5-Year Estimates
